ForgeZero package manager

ForgeZero packages are verified with trusted-key checks before installation.

Trust model

- Package manifests must include a signature field.
- The signature key must be present in the trusted-key store.
- Untrusted keys are rejected before a package is accepted.

Commands

- fz pm trust <key> - add a key to the trust store
- fz pm keys - list trusted keys
- fz pm verify <package> - verify a package manifest
- fz pm install <package> - install a package after verification

Example

fz pm trust demo-key
fz pm verify ./pkg
fz pm install ./pkg